2) Starting this Monday, 8/9, we will be expanding our open hours & days. We'll be adding Monday-Wednesday back into the mix. Our kitchen will not be open on these days. If we do not have a food truck available on those days, you will be allowed to order/bring food. Our kitchen will still remain open Thursday-Sunday.

To summarize, here are our new hours:
Monday-Wednesday: 4-8pm (kitchen closed)
Thursday: 4-8pm
Friday: 4-9pm
Saturday: 1-9pm
Sunday: 1-8pm

Friendly reminder that masks are required when you are not seated.

We hope to see you at our Tasting Room & Kitchen soon!

node.text:
Potato, Potata does not apply here. 🚫 There is nothing basic about this dish from Chef Charis.

The Smoked Potatoes are confit>smoked>smashed>roasted. From there they are tossed with black garlic-tomato vinaigrette, which is made of fermented black garlic, sun dried tomatoes, smoked paprika, sherry vinegar, and maple syrup. Served with spiced seeds and a cashew based ranch dip made from cashews, dill, thyme, rice vinegar, onion and garlic powder, nutritional yeast, and water. This delicious starter is both vegan and gluten free.

Looking for a pairing? We recommend @hellofriendbeer I Feel Better Now: A Hazy IPA with Citra and Nelson Sauvin. 6.8% ABV

Swing by our Tasting Room & Kitchen this weekend to try Chef's Smoked Potatoes.

Beer release today! We can’t recommend strongly enough that you watch ‘til the end to see the color of this beer. It’s a real beaut.
 
Flying Lizard is a Golden Sour Beer Aged in Oak Barrels with Lychee and Red Dragon Fruit.
 
Born from the fiery Red Dragon Fruit and the tropical behemoth that is Lychee, Flying Lizard is a fantastical beast of a beer. Golden sour beer was aged in oak barrels for a collective of nine months before introducing it to the aberrant fruits for secondary fermentation. After another three months of conditioning, the result is a beer with a brilliant ruby red hue and the most hyper tropical fruit aromatics. We are happy to finally unleash Flying Lizard. 7.9% ABV
 
Tasting Room: We’ll have bottles for sale as well as draft pours & crowlers.
 
Online Beer Shop: Head to the link in our bio to order for shipping to a residential or business address in California.

node.text:
New menu item from Chef Charis deserving of a round of applause. 
 
Pulled Pork Flatbread with cornbread purée, pickled green tomatoes, white cheddar, torpedo onions, and comeback sauce.
 
A few words from Chef:
 
“The pork is slow cooked overnight until it’s shreddable. For the sauce I make cornbread and then purée it with additional dairy to a creamy consistency. Thinly sliced pickled green tomatoes are layered over a white cheddar and mozzarella cheese blend with shaved red torpedo onions. It’ll be finished with comeback sauce and crispy onions.”
 
Looking to pair it with one of our beers? We recommend Cosmic Dust, a Golden Sour Beer Aged in Oak Barrels with Hibiscus.
 
Swing by our tasting Room & Kitchen to try Chef’s scrumptious Pulled Pork Flatbread.

Who put all this artwork in the cooler?!
 
@hellofriendbeer has taken over our cooler. All 3 beers are freshly canned and ready for release during the Launch Party and Can Release tomorrow (7/10). What you see is what we’ve got, so get here early if you’d like to get your hands on some cans. Here is what we’ve got in store for you:
 
🧑‍🚀Don’t Drink the Water | Hazy DIPA with Galaxy, Citra, and Simcoe | 8.8% ABV | Art by @mllrcreative
 
Don’t Drink the Water was brewed with two-row Malt, Golden Promise, malted oats, and wheat malt creating a plush and full bodied base for a heavy handed dose of Galaxy, Citra and Simcoe. Loaded with pungent tropical aromas reminiscent of papaya, cherimoya and guava this beer pops with bright and bold characteristics. Layered with notes of freshly peeled grapefruit and over-ripe passionfruit, Don’t Drink the Water is a deluge of aroma and flavor.
 
👍I Feel Better Now | Hazy IPA with Citra and Nelson Sauvin | 6.8% ABV | Art by @artbyderv
 
Brewed with pilsner malt, malted oats, and wheat malt, I Feel Better Now exudes a thick and creamy body that serves as a beautiful canvas for Citra and Nelson Sauvin. Tones of green papaya and bright starfruit are backed by bold aromas of overripe guava and macerated pineapple creating an absolute joy ride for your senses.
 
🌳Saturday In The Park | Unfiltered Pilsner | 5.1% ABV | Art by @jazmn_camille
 
Saturday In the Park is simplicity at its finest. Brewed with 100% pilsner malt and hopped singularly with low-alpha Saaz, this beer is a straightforward presentation of a simple yet beautiful lager. Light floral components backed with an ever so slight bitterness makes this our most quaffable beer to date. Crisp, clean, and quenching, this is the beer we all reach for.

Cans will be released when the party starts at 1pm tomorrow, Saturday, July 10th. See you soon!
